@NODE GAD_M_Add "Add a league"

 @{b}Add@{ub}

  Add a new league to the list of leagues. The 'Add league' window will
  pop up with a number of options to set for the league:

  @{b}Name of league@{ub}

   The name of the league. E.g. 'Premier league', 'Bundesliga'.

  @{b}Number of teams@{ub}

   The number of teams in the league.

  @{b}Points for a home win@{ub}

   The points given for a home victory.

  @{b}Points for a home draw@{ub}

   The points given for a home draw.

  @{b}Points for an away win@{ub}

   The points given for a away victory.

  @{b}Points for an away draw@{ub}

   The points given for a away draw.

  @{b}Play twice@{ub}

   In some leagues the teams plays twice against eachother both at home
   and away so tick this gadget if this is the case for the league you are
   about to add.


  Press 'Okay' to add the league to the list. Press 'Cancel' to abort.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GAD_M_Remove "Remove a league"

 @{b}Remove@{ub}

  Removes the highlighted league without any warning.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GAD_M_Sort "Sort leagues"

 @{b}Sort@{ub}

  Sort the leauges by name.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GAD_M_Up "Move a league up"

 @{b}Up@{ub}

  Moves the highlighted league upwards in the list.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GAD_M_Down "Move a league down"

 @{b}Down@{ub}

  Moves the highlighted league downwards in the list.
@ENDNODE

@NODE TeamWindow "Team window usage"

 @{b}Team window usage@{ub}

  @{b}Menus@{ub}

   @{" Project       " LINK MENU_T_Project}
   @{" Teams         " LINK MENU_T_Teams}
   @{" Results       " LINK MENU_T_Results}
   @{" Sort          " LINK MENU_T_Sort}
   @{" Graph         " LINK MENU_T_Graph}
   @{" Miscellaneous " LINK MENU_T_Miscellaneous}
   @{" Print         " LINK MENU_T_Print}

  @{b}Gadgets@{ub}

   @{" Add... " LINK GAD_T_Add}
   @{" Remove " LINK GAD_T_Remove}
   @{" Sort   " LINK GAD_T_Sort}
   @{" Up     " LINK GAD_T_Up}
   @{" Down   " LINK GAD_T_Down}

  By double clicking on a team you can enter a new result. @{" Add result " LINK MI_T_ResultsAdd}

  Pressing return while a team is highlighted you will get the team
  information window. @{" Team information " LINK MI_T_TeamInformation}

  Above the listview there are a number of characters and a single word :)
  They are common abbrevations and you should be familiar with most of
  them:

   P    - Position
   Name - Name of the team

   M    - Matches played
   W    - Total number of won matches
   D    - Total number of drawn matches
   L    - Total number of lost matches
   F    - Total number of goals scored (for)
   A    - Total number of goals conceded (against)
   P    - Total number of points

   W    - Number of won matches home
   D    - Number of drawn matches home
   L    - Number of lost matches home
   F    - Number of goals scored home (for)
   A    - Number of goals conceded home (against)
   P    - Number of points gained by home matches

   W    - Number of won matches away
   D    - Number of drawn matches away
   L    - Number of lost matches away
   F    - Number of goals scored away (for)
   A    - Number of goals conceded away (against)
   P    - Number of points gained by away matches
@ENDNODE

