@NODE MI_T_Quit "Project menu"

 @{b}Quit@{ub}

  Quits the team window and returns to the leagues window.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_FormTotal "Teams menu"

 @{b}Form@{ub}

  Use this function when you want to get a picture of how a team is
  currently doing. A requester appears where you'll have to type the
  number of matches back Leagues should look at when generating the form
  table. F.x. if you typed 5 you will get a table which represents how the
  league would look like if each team had only played 5 matches. A teams
  form usually varies during a season so this is a very important feature
  to have.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_FormHome "Teams menu"

 @{b}Form home@{ub}

  See @{" Form " LINK MI_T_FormTotal} for a more detailed description of this feature.

  A form table is only generated for the last x number of home matches.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_FormAway "Teams menu"

 @{b}Form away@{ub}

  See @{" Form " LINK MI_T_FormTotal} for a more detailed description of this feature.

  A form table is only generated for the last x number of away matches.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_AverageGoalsScoredTotal "Teams menu"

 @{b}Average goals scored total@{ub}

  Opens a window with the average goals scored by each team in the league.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_AverageGoalsScoredHome "Teams menu"

 @{b}Average goals scored home@{ub}

  Opens a window with the average goals scored by each team in the league
  home.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_AverageGoalsScoredAway "Teams menu"

 @{b}Average goals scored away@{ub}

  Opens a window with the average goals scored by each team in the league
  away.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_AverageGoalsScoredPeriod "Teams menu"

 @{b}Average goals scored period@{ub}

  Opens a window with the average goals scored by each team in the league
  in a certain period determined by the values you enter in the period
  requester.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_AverageGoalsConcededTotal "Teams menu"

 @{b}Average goals conceded total@{ub}

  Opens a window with the average goals conceded by each team in the
  league.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_AverageGoalsConcededHome "Teams menu"

 @{b}Average goals conceded home@{ub}

  Opens a window with the average goals conceded by each team in the
  league home.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_AverageGoalsConcededAway "Teams menu"

 @{b}Average goals conceded away@{ub}

  Opens a window with the average goals conceded by each team in the
  league away.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_AverageGoalsConcededPeriod "Teams menu"

 @{b}Average goals conceded period@{ub}

  Opens a window with the average goals conceded by each team in the
  league in a certain period determined by the values you enter in the
  period requester.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_ResultsAdd "Results menu"

 @{b}Add@{ub}

  Add a result. Input the goals scored by the teams in the number gadgets
  to the right and press Okay to accept them.

  The number of goals scored by a team may not be higher than 20.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_ResultsRemove "Results menu"

 @{b}Remove@{ub}

  Remove a result. Select the result to remove in the results window by
  pressing return. Press escape to cancel the operation.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_ResultsChange "Results menu"

 @{b}Change@{ub}

  Change a result. Select the result to change in the results window by
  pressing return. Enter the new result and press escape.

  The number of goals scored by a team may not be higher than 20.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_ResultsShowForSelectedTeam "Results menu"

 @{b}Show for selected team@{ub}

  Will show the highlighted teams results in a window. The first result is
  the team's first match and so forth.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_ResultsShowForAllTeams "Results menu"

 @{b}Show for all teams@{ub}

  Shows the results for all teams in the league.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_ResultsStatisticsLeague "Results menu"

 @{b}Statistics league@{ub}

  Shows various statistical information on the league.
  
  First is the result matrix. The vertical row of numbers represents the
  number of goals scored home in a result. The horizontal is the number of
  goals conceded away in a result. Each number in the matrix represents
  how many times the result has occured in the league.
  
  Next is the total number of goals scored by all teams home, away and in
  total.
  
  Last is the number of outcomes (home wins, away wins and draws).
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_ResultsStatisticsSelectedTeam "Results menu"

 @{b}Statistics selected team@{ub}

  Shows various statistical information on the league.
  
  First is the result matrix. The vertical row of numbers represents the
  number of goals scored home in a result. The horizontal is the number of
  goals conceded away in a result. Each number in the matrix represents
  how many times the result has occured for the team in question.
  
  Next is the total number of goals scored by the team home, away and in
  total.
  
  Last is the number of outcomes (home wins, away wins and draws).
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortName "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by name@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league alphabetically.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortPointsTotal "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by points@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by points. If two teams have the same
  number of points the team with the best score difference will be moved
  upwards. If they also have the same score difference nothing will
  happen.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortPointsHome "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by points home@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by points home. If two teams have the same
  number of points the team with the best score difference will be moved
  upwards. If they also have the same score difference nothing will
  happen.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortPointsAway "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by points away@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by points away. If two teams have the same
  number of points the team with the best score difference will be moved
  upwards. If they also have the same score difference nothing will
  happen.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortWinsTotal "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by wins@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the total number of wins.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortWinsHome "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by home wins@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the number of wins home.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortWinsAway "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by away wins@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the number of wins away.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortDrawnTotal "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by draws@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the total number of drawn matches.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortDrawnHome "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by draws at home@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the number of drawn home matches.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortDrawnAway "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by away draws@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the number of drawn away matches.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortLossesTotal "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by losses@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the total number of losses.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortLossesHome "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by losses home@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the number of lost matches home.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortLossesAway "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by losses away@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the number of lost matches away.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortGoalsScoredTotal "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by goals scored@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the total number of goals scored.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortGoalsScoredHome "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by goals scored home@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the number of goals scored home.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortGoalsScoredAway "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by scored away@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the number of goals scored away.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortGoalsConcededTotal "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by goals conceded@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the total number of goals conceded.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortGoalsConcededHome "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by goals conceded home@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the number of goals conceded home.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_SortGoalsConcededAway "Sort menu"

 @{b}Sort by goals against away@{ub}

  Sort the teams in the league by the number of goals conceded away.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_GraphGoalsScoredAllTeams "Graph menu"

 @{b}Goals scored by all teams@{ub}

  Shows a graph of all goals scored by all teams in the leauge. The x-axis
  represents the match number and the y-axis represents the number of
  goals scored.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_GraphGoalsScoredSelectedTeam "Graph menu"

 @{b}Goals scored by selected team@{ub}

  Shows a graph of all goals scored by the team selected. The x-axis
  represents the match number and the y-axis represents the number of
  goals scored.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_GraphGoalsConcededAllTeams "Graph menu"

 @{b}Goals conceded by all teams@{ub}

  Shows a graph of all goals conceded by all teams in the leauge. The
  x-axis represents the match number and the y-axis represents the number
  of goals conceded.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_GraphGoalsConcededSelectedTeam "Graph menu"

 @{b}Goals conceded by selected team@{ub}

  Shows a graph of all goals conceded by the team selected. The x-axis
  represents the match number and the y-axis represents the number of
  goals conceded.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_TeamInformation "Miscellaneous menu"

 @{b}Team information@{ub}

  Information on the highlighted team will be shown in a window. The first
  information is the teams best and worst matches. Then the form of the
  team expressed via 'w','d','l','W',D','L' for respectively home wins,
  home draws, home defeats, away wins, away draws, away defeats.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_GoalDifferences "Miscellaneous menu"

 @{b}Goal differences@{ub}

  Shows a window with the goal differences for each team (a goal
  difference is simply the total number of goals conceded by a team
  subtracted from the total number of goals scored by a team) in a sorted
  manner meaning the team with the best goal difference in top.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_PrintTableTotal "Print menu"

 @{b}Print@{ub}

  Prints the table as it is represented in the team window.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_PrintTableHome "Print menu"

 @{b}Print@{ub}

  Prints the table as it is represented in the team window but only the
  data for home matches is printed.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_PrintTableAway "Print menu"

 @{b}Print@{ub}

  Prints the table as it is represented in the team window but only the
  data for away matches is printed.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_PrintResultsAllTeams "Print menu"

 @{b}Print@{ub}

  Prints the results for all teams.
@ENDNODE

@NODE MI_T_PrintResultsSelectedTeam "Print menu"

 @{b}Print@{ub}

  Prints the results for the selected team.
@ENDNODE

#
# END OF TEAM MENUS
# START OF TEAM GADGETS
#

@NODE GAD_T_Add "Add a team"

 @{b}Add@{ub}

  Before you may start adding results to the league you must have created
  all the teams in the league. Just type the name in the requester and the
  team is now in the league. To remove a team first highligt it, then
  press @{"Remove" LINK GAD_T_Remove}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GAD_T_Remove "Remove a team"

 @{b}Remove@{ub}

  Removes the highlighted team. You can only remove a team if there have
  not been adding any results to the league.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GAD_T_Sort "Sort teams"

 @{b}Sort@{ub}

  Sort the teams by points. This is actually just a shortcut for the sort
  menuitem @{"Sort/Points/Total" LINK MI_T_SortPointsTotal}
@ENDNODE

@NODE GAD_T_Up "Move a team up"

 @{b}Up@{ub}

  Moves the highlighted team upwards in the list. Use this if you f.x.
  want to compare two teams with eachother. Move the two teams towards
  eachother so it is easier to compare their data.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GAD_T_Down "Move a team down"

 @{b}Down@{ub}

  Moves the highlighted team downwards in the list. Use this if you f.x.
  want to compare two teams with eachother. Move the two teams towards
  eachother so it's easier to compare their data.
@ENDNODE

#
# END OF TEAM GADGETS
#

@NODE HowToRegister "HowToRegister"

 @{b}How to register Leagues@{ub}

  To register, FIRST fill out the registration form which is included in
  the distribution as @{b}Leagues.regform@{ub} and send it to me to one of the
  addresses below.

  THEN there are 3 ways you can send the registration fee to me.

  @{b}1.@{ub} The first and easiest way (in my opinion) is to send cash to my
     snailmail address below.

     But keep in mind that it is at your own risk if you do that. I cannot
     be responsible for lost letters. But just remember to wrap a piece
     of paper around the cash so the possibly corrupt mailman is unable
     to see what is inside the envelope.

     The registration fee may be one of the following:

       50,- DKR (Danish kroners)
       50,- SKR (Swedish kroners)
       50,- NKR (Norwegian kroners)
       15,- DEM (German D-mark)
       10,- USD (US-Dollars)
        5,- GBP (British pound sterling)

      or the same amount as 50 DKR in any other currency!

     No coins (except Danish) accepted!!

  @{b}2.@{ub} Eurocheque

     Send a Eurocheque payable to 'Martin Wulffeld' with the amount of
     50 DKR (Danish kroners).
     
     If you send any other kind of cheque please include an extra
     50 DKR since the bank charges outrageous fees.

  @{b}3.@{ub} Transfer the equivalent of 50,- DKR to my bank:

      Unibank
      Praestoe Afdeling
      Adelgade 76
      4720 Praestoe
      Denmark

      Name: Martin Wulffeld

      Reg. number:    0047
      Account number: 4482-600-846

 ===========================================================================

  ASAP on receipt of your registration I will send a personalized keyfile
  to you on a disk. But things take time so please allow up to 8 weeks for
  delivery, thanks = absolute, extremely worst case. Usually from you
  sending the registration till you get the key will not take more than 2
  weeks.

  Put the keyfile in your L: assign or the path where Leagues is started from.

  You may not sell or give away the keyfile. The keyfile will make all
  (future) locked features available to you.

 ===========================================================================

  - Snail mail: Martin Wulffeld
                Odensevej 121, 2 TV
                4700 Naestved
                Denmark

  - Internet:   -

  - FidoNet:    2:236/25.4

  - AmigaNet:   39:141/132.4

  - Phone:      +45 (55) 77 01 37
@ENDNODE

@NODE WhatDoIGet "What do I get?"

 @{b}If I register what do I get?@{ub}

  - Access to all (future) locked features via the keyfile you will get.

  - A disk with the latest version of Leagues, Xtruder, Vinci and other
    of my recent productions.
@ENDNODE

